data.name: Black Bean Burger
data.quickTastyDescription: Delicious, hearty black bean burger packed with flavor and perfect for a satisfying meal.
detailedCookingInstructions: In a bowl, mash the black beans with a fork until mostly smooth, leaving some chunks for texture.
Mix in the bread crumbs, egg, chopped onion, minced garlic, cumin, salt, and pepper until well combined.
Form the mixture into two patties.
Heat olive oil in a pan over medium heat and cook the patties for about 5-7 minutes on each side until golden brown.
Toast the burger buns lightly on the same pan if desired.
Assemble the burger by placing the patty on the bun, adding lettuce and tomato slices on top.
data.modifiersForBase: Add toppings like avocado or cheese if desired.
